65\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/knsbackend-300x165.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/knsbackend-1024x562.png 1024w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/knsbackend.png 1130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Included is is the new version of the <a class=\"http\" href=\"http:\/\/jontheechidna.wordpress.com\/2013\/04\/03\/muon-suite-2-0-0-released\/\">Muon Suite<\/a> for app install and upgrades. It introduces support\u00a0for installing Plasma widgets found in KDE&#8217;s KNewStuff framework\u00a0from within Software Center and Muon Discover.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Rekonq_2\">Rekonq 2<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/kubwp.kubuntu.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Rekonq221.png\" rel=\"lightbox[854]\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright wp-image-2052 size-medium\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Rekonq221-300x178.png\" alt=\"Rekonq221\" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Rekonq221-300x178.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Rekonq221.png 635w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p><a class=\"http\" href=\"http:\/\/adjamblog.wordpress.com\/2012\/12\/29\/rekonq-2-0-first-stable\/\"><br \/>\nRekonq 2<\/a><\/p>\n<p>Version 2 of our web browser adds a bunch of new\u00a0features<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>inline spellcheck<\/li>\n<li>new incognito mode<\/li>\n<li>new startup option: incognito URL<\/li>\n<li>new startup option: webapp URL<\/li>\n<li>pinning tabs<\/li>\n<li>improved error page<\/li>\n<li>simplified rekonq pages<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Homerun\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2053\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/homerun-300x188.png\" alt=\"homerun\" width=\"300\" height=\"188\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/homerun-300x188.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/homerun-1024x640.png 1024w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/homerun.png 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>Homerun<\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>A full screen alternative to the Kickoff\u00a0application menu, add it to your panel to give it a try.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Screen_Management\">Screen Management<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2055\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/kscreen-288x300.png\" alt=\"kscreen\" width=\"288\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/kscreen-288x300.png 288w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/kscreen.png 611w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 288px) 100vw, 288px\" \/><\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>A new screen management tools makes it easy to\u00a0attach and unattach extra monitors.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Oxygen_Sans_Font\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2056\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/oxygen-font-300x181.png\" alt=\"oxygen-font\" width=\"300\" height=\"181\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/oxygen-font-300x181.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/oxygen-font.png 903w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>Oxygen Sans Font<\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Available on the default install is Oxygen Sans,\u00a0a new font from KDE&#8217;s artists.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<h3 id=\"Krita\">Krita<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-2057\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/krita-300x253.png\" alt=\"krita\" width=\"300\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/krita-300x253.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/krita.png 892w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/h3>\n<p>Our painting application Krita now uses a nifty\u00a0new calculations library Vc making it twice as fast as before. It\u00a0also sports an artsy new black theme.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Installer\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2058\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/ubiquity-300x171.png\" alt=\"ubiquity\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/ubiquity-300x171.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/ubiquity.png 994w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>Installer<\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>Our installer sports a professional new look<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"LibreOffice_4\">LibreOffice 4<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"\/LibreOffice\">LibreOffice<\/a> has been\u00a0upgraded to <a class=\"http\" href=\"http:\/\/www.libreoffice.org\/download\/4-0-new-features-and-fixes\/\">Version\u00a04.0.1.2<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"MTP_Devices\">MTP Devices<\/h3>\n<p>Access your digital music player and smartphone\u00a0through MTP protocol.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Tomahawk\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2059\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/tomahawk-300x230.png\" alt=\"tomahawk\" width=\"300\" height=\"230\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/tomahawk-300x230.png 300w, https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/tomahawk.png 925w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>Tomahawk<\/h3>\n<p>Available in the archives is <a class=\"http\" href=\"http:\/\/tomahawk-player.org\">Tomahawk<\/a>, a new music player\u00a0which makes it easy to share your music with your friends over IM.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><\/h2>\n<h2 id=\"Infrastructure\">Infrastructure<\/h2>\n<p>For full details of software included see\u00a0<a class=\"http\" href=\"http:\/\/distrowatch.com\/table.php?distribution=kubuntu\">Kubuntu on\u00a0Distrowatch<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Secure_Boot\">Secure Boot<\/h3>\n<p>Kubuntu should now be able to support <a class=\"https\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Unified_Extensible_Firmware_Interface#Secure_boot\">UEFI Secure Boot<\/a>, a standard for controlling what software can\u00a0be run on a computer. Supporting Secure Boot, a part of the Windows\u00a08 certification requirements for client systems, ensures that\u00a0Ubuntu will continue to provide an &#8220;it just works&#8221; experience on\u00a0new hardware.<\/p>\n<p>If you have hardware for this, we would\u00a0appreciate your help in testing it out.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h1 id=\"Known_Problems\">Known Problems<\/h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"interwiki\" title=\"Bug\" href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/bugs\/1172534\">1172534<\/a>\u00a0plymouth boot splash does not show on an installed system<\/li>\n<li><a class=\"interwiki\" title=\"Bug\" href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/bugs\/1164236\">1164236<\/a>\u00a013.04 beta 2 plasma active crashes on startup<\/li>\n<li><a class=\"interwiki\" title=\"Bug\" href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/bugs\/1164239\">1164239<\/a>\u00a0ubiquity does not start on kubuntu 13.04 arm image<\/li>\n<li><a class=\"interwiki\" title=\"Bug\" href=\"https:\/\/bugs.launchpad.net\/bugs\/1172161\">1172161<\/a>\u00a0Icon &#8220;Install Kubuntu 13.04&#8221; won&#8217;t run in live session on PowerPC<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Information on installing Kubuntu 13.04 on PowerPC systems can be found <a class=\"https\" href=\"https:\/\/wiki.kubuntu.org\/Kubuntu\/PowerPC\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h1 id=\"Feedback\">Feedback<\/h1>\n<p>We want to hear your opinions on this release.<\/p>\n<p>You can give us feedback on the <a class=\"https\" href=\"https:\/\/plus.google.com\/107577785796696065138\">Kubuntu\u00a0Google+<\/a> page. Your input is an invaluable resource